titleInfo.title: AG Environmental Products v. World Energy Alternatives
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER, The parties shall file a joint stipulation for dismissal (or other dispositivestipulation) with the clerk of the court which will fully dispose of the case on or beforeJanuary 31, 2008. If the case is being dismissed, the stipulation shall comply with Fed.R. Civ. P. 41(a)(1)(ii) and shall state whether the dismissal is with or without prejudice.2. Absent compliance with this order, this case (including all counterclaims andthe like) may be dismissed without further notice in accordance with NECivR 68.1. ( Dismissal Papers Deadline due by 1/31/2008.) Ordered by Magistrate Judge Thomas D. Thalken. (PCV, )
